    "2 and 3 indicate that to match the performance of the sMTJ-based p-bits, more sophisticated PRNGs like Xoshiro must be used.",
    "In this case, merely the PRNG cost of a 32-bit Xoshiro is 7516 transistors.",
    "The LUT costs are the same as LFSRbased p-bits which is about ≈4029 transistors.",
    "Collectively, these results indicate that to truly replicate the performance of an sMTJ-based p-bit, the actual transistor cost of a digital design is ~11,000 transistors which is an order of magnitude worse than the conservative estimation performed in ref. 28.",
